\section{Configuration Management}
\label{track:configuration}

The track system uses nytid's configuration system (via typerconf) to store user
preferences and data locations, making it configurable and consistent with other
nytid components.

The track system supports the following configuration options:

\begin{description}
\item[[[track.data_dir]]] Directory where tracking data is stored.
  Defaults to \texttt{\~{}/.nytid/tracking} if not configured.
\item[[[track.weekly_limit]]] Default weekly hour limit for warnings
  in statistics. Defaults to 40.0 hours if not configured.
\item[[[track.daily_limit]]] Default daily hour limit for warnings
  in statistics. Defaults to 8.0 hours if not configured.
\item[[[track.auto-suspend.default]]] Whether to automatically
  suspend tracking when a tmux pane loses focus and resume when it
  regains focus.  Defaults to \enquote{true}.  Can be overridden
  per launch with [[--auto-suspend]]/[[--no-auto-suspend]].
  Requires tmux [[focus-events]] to be on.
\item[[[track.auto-suspend.<worker>]]] Per-worker override for
  auto-suspend.  Set to \enquote{false} for automated workers like
  \enquote{dan-claude} that do not interactively focus tmux
  windows.  Example:
  [[nytid config track.auto-suspend.dan-claude -s false]].
\item[[[track.debug]]] Enable deferred window-event debug logging and
  notifications.  Defaults to \enquote{false}.  Truthy values are
  \enquote{true}, \enquote{1}, and \enquote{yes}.
\end{description}

To customize the track system, use the standard nytid config commands:

\begin{minted}{bash}
# Set custom data directory
nytid config track.data_dir -s /path/to/custom/tracking/data

# Set weekly hour limit for work-life balance warnings  
nytid config track.weekly_limit -s 35.0

# Set daily hour limit warnings
nytid config track.daily_limit -s 7.5

# Disable auto-suspend for an automated worker
nytid config track.auto-suspend.dan-claude -s false

# Enable deferred window-event debugging
nytid config track.debug -s true

# View current track configuration
nytid config track.data_dir
nytid config track.weekly_limit  
nytid config track.daily_limit
nytid config track.debug
\end{minted}

The configuration system ensures that track settings are persistent and can be
customized per user or per course context, following nytid's standard patterns.

We use nytid's StorageRoot system for managing tracking data files, which provides
a consistent interface with other nytid components and supports different storage
backends (local filesystem, AFS, etc.).

The storage-root helper is the only code that cares about where track
data lives, so we introduce [[TRACKING_DIR_CONFIG]] here rather than in
one distant global block.

<<constants>>=
TRACKING_DIR_CONFIG = "track.data_dir"
@

<<configuration management>>=
def get_tracking_storage() -> storage.StorageRoot:
    """
    Get the StorageRoot for tracking data.
    
    Uses nytid's StorageRoot system for consistent file management.
    Returns a StorageRoot object that can be used to open tracking data files.
    """
    try:
        tracking_dir = pathlib.Path(config.get(TRACKING_DIR_CONFIG))
    except KeyError:
        # Fallback to default location in user's home directory
        tracking_dir = pathlib.Path.home() / ".nytid" / "tracking"
        # Set the default in config for future use
        config.set(TRACKING_DIR_CONFIG, str(tracking_dir))
    
    return storage.StorageRoot(tracking_dir)

def get_tracking_dir() -> pathlib.Path:
    """Get the tracking data directory path (for compatibility)"""
    return get_tracking_storage()._StorageRoot__path

def get_tracking_data_file() -> pathlib.Path:
    """Get the path to the tracking data file"""
    return get_tracking_dir() / "tracking_data.json"

def get_tracking_lock_file() -> pathlib.Path:
    """Get the path to the tracking history lock file."""
    return get_tracking_dir() / "tracking_data.lock"


def get_tmux_context_lock_file() -> pathlib.Path:
    """Return the lock file guarding tmux context state."""
    return get_tracking_dir() / "tmux_context.lock"

def sanitize_who(who: str) -> str:
    """Sanitize a worker name for use in filenames.

    Lowercases the name, keeps alphanumerics and hyphens,
    replaces everything else with underscores.
    """
    return "".join(
        c if c.isalnum() or c == "-" else "_"
        for c in who.lower()
    )

def sanitize_tmux_id(value: str) -> str:
    """Sanitize a tmux identifier for use in filenames."""
    return "".join(
        c if c.isalnum() or c == "-" else "_"
        for c in value
    )

def build_tmux_server_key(
    hostname: str,
    socket_path: str,
) -> str:
    """Return a stable key for one tmux server."""
    digest = hashlib.sha256(
        f"{hostname}\0{socket_path}".encode()
    ).hexdigest()
    return digest[:16]

def parse_tmux_socket_path(
    tmux_env: Optional[str],
) -> Optional[str]:
    """Extract the tmux socket path from ``$TMUX`` if present."""
    if not tmux_env:
        return None
    try:
        socket_path, _server_pid, _session_idx = tmux_env.rsplit(",", 2)
    except ValueError:
        return tmux_env or None
    return socket_path or None

def get_current_tmux_server_key() -> Optional[str]:
    """Return the current tmux server key from the environment."""
    socket_path = parse_tmux_socket_path(
        os.environ.get("TMUX")
    )
    if not socket_path:
        return None
    return build_tmux_server_key(
        socket.gethostname(), socket_path,
    )

def get_current_session_file(
    who: str = None
) -> pathlib.Path:
    """Get the path to the current session file for a worker."""
    if who is None:
        who = default_username
    tracking_dir = get_tracking_dir()
    suffix = sanitize_who(who)
    session_file = tracking_dir / f"current_session_{suffix}.json"

    # Backward compatibility: migrate old unsuffixed file
    if who == default_username and not session_file.exists():
        old_file = tracking_dir / "current_session.json"
        if old_file.exists():
            return old_file

    return session_file

def get_current_session_lock_file(
    who: str = None
) -> pathlib.Path:
    """Get the lock file guarding one worker's active session."""
    session_file = get_current_session_file(who)
    return session_file.with_suffix(".lock")
@

