Tracked window launches need one stronger serialization guarantee than
steady-state hooks.  The [[tmux new-window]] command itself may spawn a
[[session-window-changed]] hook before we have written the new window's
labels and updated [[last_selected_window]].  We therefore hold the
tmux-context lock across a narrow \enquote{hook-observability} phase
that covers [[new-window]], label publication, and the
[[last_selected_window]] write.

The lock begins before invoking [[tmux new-window]] so any detached
hook spawned by that command is forced to wait on the flock before it
can snapshot tmux-context state.  We release the lock as soon as
[[last_selected_window]] has been updated: from that moment on, the
[[prev == selected]] guard in [[window_switch_detached]] already
discards any redundant hook event, so keeping the lock held any longer
serves no purpose.

Crucially, we must not hold the tmux-context lock across
[[seed_window_event_buffer]].  On the [[from-untracked]] path, the
seed's self-trigger calls [[start_tracking_labels]], which delegates to
[[mutate_worker_tracking_state]]---and that function acquires the
tmux-context lock internally via its own [[open]] plus [[fcntl.flock]].
Linux [[flock]] is associated with the open file description, not the
process: a second [[open]] on the same path from the same process gets
an independent lock and blocks waiting for the first to release.
Holding the context lock across the seed therefore self-deadlocks the
tracked-window launch path.  Splitting the phases keeps the narrow
serialization intact while letting the seed acquire the context lock
cleanly.

We also install the new pane's sync and cleanup hooks outside the
context lock.  Those calls are just [[tmux set-hook]] invocations; they
publish no hook-observable state that needs the lock.  The brief gap
between lock release and [[install_tmux_window_sync_hooks]] is benign:
the only events that could fire in that gap are [[pane-focus-in]] on
the new pane (which has no hooks yet, so nothing to dispatch) and
[[session-window-changed]] (whose detached body now sees
[[prev == selected]] and discards).

<<launch tmux command and install hooks>>=
needs_finalize = False
source_is_tracked = False
source_window_id = None

def launch_and_publish_state():
    nonlocal pane_id, window_id, session_id
    nonlocal needs_finalize, source_is_tracked, source_window_id

    result = subprocess.run(
        tmux_args,
        check=True,
        capture_output=True,
        text=True,
    )
    pane_info = result.stdout.strip().split()
    if pane_info:
        pane_id = pane_info[0]
    if len(pane_info) > 1:
        window_id = pane_info[1]
    if len(pane_info) > 2:
        session_id = pane_info[2]
    install_tmux_exit_hooks(pane_id, hook_command)
    if focus_labels and focus_who:
        if not tmux_server_key:
            raise RuntimeError(
                "tmux server key missing for auto-suspend launch"
            )
        if focus_window and window_id and session_id:
            write_window_labels(
                window_id,
                focus_who,
                tmux_server_key,
                focus_labels,
            )
            prev_wid = read_last_selected_window(
                focus_who,
                tmux_server_key,
                session_id,
            )
            source_window_id = prev_wid
            source_is_tracked = (
                prev_wid is not None
                and read_window_labels(
                    prev_wid,
                    focus_who,
                    tmux_server_key,
                )
                is not None
            )
            write_last_selected_window(
                focus_who,
                tmux_server_key,
                session_id,
                window_id,
            )
            needs_finalize = True
        else:
            write_pane_labels(
                pane_id,
                focus_who,
                tmux_server_key,
                focus_labels,
            )
            install_tmux_focus_hooks(
                pane_id,
                focus_who,
                tmux_server_key,
            )
            install_tmux_suspend_cleanup_hook(
                pane_id,
                focus_who,
                tmux_server_key,
            )

if focus_window and focus_labels and focus_who:
    with_tmux_context_lock(launch_and_publish_state)
else:
    launch_and_publish_state()

if needs_finalize:
    if source_is_tracked:
        seed_event_lines = [
            build_window_switch_event_line(
                target_tracked=True,
                source_tracked=True,
                source_window_id=source_window_id,
                target_window_id=window_id,
            ),
        ]
    else:
        seed_event_lines = [
            build_window_event_line(
                "start",
                focus_labels,
                window_id=window_id,
            ),
            build_window_switch_event_line(
                target_tracked=True,
                source_tracked=False,
                source_window_id=source_window_id,
                target_window_id=window_id,
            ),
        ]
    seed_window_event_buffer(
        focus_who,
        tmux_server_key,
        session_id,
        seed_event_lines,
    )
    install_tmux_window_sync_hooks(
        session_id,
        pane_id,
        focus_who,
        tmux_server_key,
    )
    install_tmux_window_cleanup_hook(
        pane_id,
        window_id,
        focus_who,
        tmux_server_key,
        focus_labels,
