\subsubsection{Per-Window Active Labels}
\label{track:window-auto-suspend}

Window auto-suspend has different semantics from pane auto-suspend.
Instead of following terminal focus, it follows whether the tracked tmux
window is selected by any attached client.  To support that, we keep a
window-scoped labels file analogous to the pane labels file.  As with
pane state, the filename includes the tmux server key so two different
tmux servers sharing a filesystem do not reuse the same window-state
path for identical [[@...]] identifiers.

<<helper functions>>=
def window_labels_path(
    window_id: str,
    who: str,
    tmux_server_key: str,
) -> pathlib.Path:
    """Return path to a tracked window's labels file."""
    safe_window = window_id.replace("@", "window_")
    return (
        get_tracking_dir()
        / f"window_labels_{sanitize_tmux_id(tmux_server_key)}_{safe_window}"
        f"_{sanitize_who(who)}.json"
    )
@

Tmux's [[session-window-changed]] hook runs the switch command via
[[run-shell]], which spawns an asynchronous subprocess.  By the time
that subprocess queries tmux for the \enquote{last window} (via
[[$0:!]]), the pointer has already advanced---empirically, both
[[#{window_id}]] and [[$0:!]] resolve to the same window after the
switch.  We therefore maintain our own state file that records the
last selected window per session and worker.  Each invocation of
[[window_switch_detached]] reads the previous value (the source
window) and writes the current value, giving the next invocation
a reliable baseline.

<<helper functions>>=
def last_selected_window_path(
    who: str,
    tmux_server_key: str,
    session_id: str,
) -> pathlib.Path:
    """Return path to the last-selected-window state file."""
    return (
        get_tracking_dir()
        / f"last_window"
        f"_{sanitize_tmux_id(tmux_server_key)}"
        f"_{sanitize_tmux_id(session_id)}"
        f"_{sanitize_who(who)}.txt"
    )


def read_last_selected_window(
    who: str,
    tmux_server_key: str,
    session_id: str,
) -> Optional[str]:
    """Read the last-selected window ID, or ``None``."""
    path = last_selected_window_path(
        who, tmux_server_key, session_id,
    )
    try:
        text = path.read_text().strip()
        return text if text else None
    except OSError:
        return None


def write_last_selected_window(
    who: str,
    tmux_server_key: str,
    session_id: str,
    window_id: str,
) -> None:
    """Record the currently selected window ID."""
    path = last_selected_window_path(
        who, tmux_server_key, session_id,
    )
    ensure_tracking_dir()
    tmp = path.with_suffix(".tmp")
    tmp.write_text(window_id + "\n")
    tmp.rename(path)
