The same tmux hook can also ask for the previously selected window via
the special target [[session_id:!]].  We need that source window because
[[window-switch tracked]] alone is ambiguous: it may mean either
untracked-to-tracked (safe to start immediately) or tracked-to-tracked
with the [[stop]] event still in flight.  Recording the source tracking
status removes that ambiguity without forcing the focus hooks into a
single ordering.

<<helper functions>>=
def get_tmux_last_window_id(
    session_id: str,
) -> Optional[str]:
    """Return the previously selected tmux window for ``session_id``."""
    try:
        result = subprocess.run(
            [
                "tmux",
                "display-message",
                "-p",
                "-t",
                f"{session_id}:!",
                "#{window_id}",
            ],
            capture_output=True,
            text=True,
            check=True,
        )
    except (subprocess.CalledProcessError, OSError):
        return None
    window_id = result.stdout.strip()
    return window_id if window_id else None
@

The switch command records both ends of the switch.  That lets the
buffer defer the tracked-to-tracked case until the matching [[stop]]
arrives, while preserving the simpler start-only behaviour for
untracked-to-tracked switches.

Because tmux's [[$0:!]] target is unreliable in [[run-shell]]
subprocesses (see the [[last_selected_window_path]] discussion above),
the switch command reads the source window from our self-managed state
file instead.  It then writes the newly selected window for the next
invocation.

When [[tmux new-window]] creates a tracked window, the parent's
launch/setup phase (see~[[<<launch tmux command and install hooks>>]])
updates [[last_selected_window]] to point to the new window and later
injects the authoritative [[window-switch]] event into the deferred
buffer via [[seed_window_event_buffer]].  Tmux may still fire
[[session-window-changed]] after the seed has already handled the
creation, causing this hook to read back the same window ID for both
source and destination.  We detect this by comparing the two IDs: a
real switch always changes the selected window, so equality means
the hook fired redundantly and should be silently discarded.

An absent selected window ID is another case where the hook must do
nothing.  [[get_tmux_selected_window_id()]] returns [[None]] when the
detached subprocess cannot read tmux state reliably---for example if the
session has already disappeared.  Treating that observation failure as a
real switch to an untracked window would spuriously stop the source
labels, so we bail out before appending any deferred event.

<<detached window switch command>>=
@cli.command(
    name="_window-switch-detached", hidden=True
)
def window_switch_detached(
    tmux_server_key: Annotated[str, tmux_server_key_opt],
    session_id: Annotated[str, session_id_opt],
    who: Annotated[str, who_opt] = default_username,
):
    """Record a deferred window-switch event."""
    selected_window_id = get_tmux_selected_window_id(
        session_id,
    )
    if selected_window_id is None:
        return
    def read_and_update():
        prev_window_id = read_last_selected_window(
            who, tmux_server_key, session_id,
        )
        if (
            prev_window_id
            and prev_window_id == selected_window_id
        ):
            return None
        if selected_window_id:
            write_last_selected_window(
                who,
                tmux_server_key,
                session_id,
                selected_window_id,
            )
        selected_is_tracked = (
            selected_window_id is not None
            and read_window_labels(
                selected_window_id,
                who,
                tmux_server_key,
            ) is not None
        )
        source_is_tracked = (
            prev_window_id is not None
            and read_window_labels(
                prev_window_id,
                who,
                tmux_server_key,
            ) is not None
        )
        return (
            selected_is_tracked,
            source_is_tracked,
            prev_window_id,
        )

    result = with_tmux_context_lock(read_and_update)
    if result is None:
        return
    (
        selected_is_tracked,
        source_is_tracked,
        prev_window_id,
    ) = result
    append_and_check_window_event(
        who,
        tmux_server_key,
        session_id,
        build_window_switch_event_line(
            target_tracked=selected_is_tracked,
            source_tracked=source_is_tracked,
            source_window_id=prev_window_id,
            target_window_id=selected_window_id,
        ),
    )
@

