\subsubsection{Shell Command Builders}

Building the shell commands that tmux hooks execute follows the
same pattern as [[build_detached_track_finalize_command]]: resolve the
current [[nytid]] entrypoint, invoke the hidden CLI command through
[[nytid track]], and pass the relevant tmux identifiers
([[pane_id]], [[session_id]], or tmux server key) plus worker identity
when needed.  Using the real CLI entrypoint instead of [[python -c]]
keeps [[typerconf]] on the same application name as interactive
[[nytid]] invocations, so detached hooks read the same configuration.

The resolution strategy also matters.  When the current process was
already launched through the real [[nytid]] script, [[sys.argv[0]]]
points at that exact entrypoint and we should reuse it so detached tmux
hooks follow the same installation the user invoked.  When the current
process was started some other way---for example from a test runner or a
different wrapper---[[sys.argv[0]]] no longer names the [[nytid]]
script.  In that case we first look for a sibling [[nytid]] script next
to [[sys.executable]], because virtualenv-based launches often sanitize
[[PATH]] but still keep the matching console script in the interpreter's
[[bin]] directory.  Only if that sibling is absent do we fall back to
[[shutil.which("nytid")]].

<<helper functions>>=
def build_detached_nytid_prefix() -> str:
    """Return the nytid CLI prefix for detached commands."""
    script_path = pathlib.Path(sys.argv[0])
    if script_path.name == "nytid" and script_path.exists():
        nytid_executable = script_path
    else:
        sibling = pathlib.Path(sys.executable).with_name("nytid")
        if sibling.exists():
            nytid_executable = sibling
        else:
            resolved = shutil.which("nytid")
            if resolved is None:
                raise RuntimeError(
                    "Unable to locate the 'nytid' executable"
                )
            nytid_executable = pathlib.Path(resolved)
    return f"{shlex.quote(str(nytid_executable))} track"
@

The pane suspend command no longer receives labels as arguments---it
reads them from the pane's active labels file (see above).  It only
needs the pane ID (to locate the file) and the worker identity.

<<helper functions>>=
def build_detached_suspend_command(
    who: str,
    pane_id: str,
    tmux_server_key: str,
) -> str:
    """Return shell command to suspend tracking on focus-out."""
    prefix = build_detached_nytid_prefix()
    cmd = (
        f"{prefix} "
        f"_suspend-detached"
        f" --pane-id {shlex.quote(pane_id)}"
        f" --server-key {shlex.quote(tmux_server_key)}"
    )
    if who != default_username:
        cmd += f" --who {shlex.quote(who)}"
    return cmd
@

