The companion window-cleanup command handles the case where the pane has
already died, so there is no live [[TMUX_PANE]] from which to recover the
window identity.  It receives the explicit [[window_id]] and removes only
the given label names from that shared window file.

<<detached finalize command>>=
@cli.command(name="_cleanup-window-detached", hidden=True)
def cleanup_window_detached(
    labels: Annotated[List[str], detached_labels_arg],
    window_id: Annotated[str, window_id_opt],
    tmux_server_key: Annotated[str, tmux_server_key_opt],
    who: Annotated[str, who_opt] = default_username,
):
    """Remove one pane's labels from tracked window state."""
    with_tmux_context_lock(
        lambda: remove_window_labels(
            window_id,
            who,
            tmux_server_key,
            list(labels),
        )
    )
