\subsubsection{Focus-Events Validation}

The [[pane-focus-out]]/[[pane-focus-in]] hooks require tmux's
[[focus-events]] option to be on.  Without it, the hooks never fire.
That breaks both pane auto-suspend and window auto-suspend, because the
window design also relies on pane-focus hooks as sensors for its
deferred event buffer.  We therefore warn at launch time whenever
auto-suspend is requested for either [[--pane]] or [[--window]] and the
option is off.

<<helper functions>>=
def warn_if_focus_events_off() -> None:
    """Emit a warning if tmux focus-events is off."""
    try:
        result = subprocess.run(
            ["tmux", "show-option", "-gv",
             "focus-events"],
            capture_output=True,
            text=True,
            check=True,
        )
        if result.stdout.strip().lower() != "on":
            typer.echo(
                "Warning: tmux focus-events is off; "
                "auto-suspend hooks will not fire.  "
                "Run: tmux set -g focus-events on",
                err=True,
            )
    except (subprocess.CalledProcessError, OSError):
        pass
