\section{Comprehensive Testing}

All test functions are defined alongside their corresponding implementation
sections throughout this document using the [[<<test functions>>]] chunk,
which is concatenated as we progress through the document. This follows
literate programming best practices by keeping tests close to the code
they validate.

Every test function takes a [[temp_tracking_dir]] fixture that redirects
all tracking I/O into a temporary directory.  The fixture is defined in
[[conftest.py]] (\cref{conftest}) so that other modules whose tests
interact with the tracking layer---such as [[todo]]
(\cref{cli.todo})---can reuse it without duplicating the patching logic.

